"{\"description\":\"We are currently looking for a number of Operatives to come and join our team within our Salisbury Depot. Based within Salisbury you'll help keep our nation moving every single day. A critical part of the work we do is the daily upkeep of the rail network. As an operative you'll work outdoors in a small team, supporting essential maintenance to keep the railway running safely and smoothly for passengers and freight users. Our operative community comes from a variety of different backgrounds, and this might be the first time that you've even considered a career in rail. We're focused on your transferrable skills and behaviours and if you can demonstrate that, then we will provide you with all the necessary training to have you working safely and competently out on the network. And if you make the grade then you can look forward to a rewarding and fulfilling career with a company that recently joined the top 50 in the Glassdoor's 2021Best Places to Work.\",\"howToApply\":\"Salary \\t \\t�29044    Been referred by a friend, then please complete this form  Network Rail Benefits:In addition, we can offer you a rewarding career with excellent benefits, including: \\t �\\t 30 days annual leave �\\t Excellent choice of pension schemes�\\t 75% subsidy on rail season tickets (including London underground)�\\t 75% off leisure rail travel for you and your family�\\t �my benefits� � our discounted online shopping site�\\t Training, development and employee assistance programme available�\\t Overtime Commitment \\t�\\t Location Allowance of �975 (South East Allowance)  Closing date: 21st November 2023  Please get your application in as soon as possible, we may close the advert before the listed closing date if we receive enough applications. Late applications will not be accepted. Please note the recruitment process for this role is a Competency based interview. Click �apply now� to apply. -   We're dedicated to creating an inclusive environment and we welcome